body:
## üéâ Description

Should we do one of below thing in `test/helpers/ether.js#ether()`?
* throw error
* convert number to string before invoke `web3.toWei(n, 'ether')`

-  [x] üìà This is a feature request.

## üíª Environment

- openzeppelin-solidity 1.12.0
- web3 0.20.6
- Truffle v4.1.14 (core: 4.1.14)
- Solidity v0.4.24 (solc-js) 

## üìù Details

I want to use helper method to convert ether value into wei, but the result is incorrect. I notice that I have to use `String` to be the parameter of `ether()`.

[helper method](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/master/test/helpers/ether.js)
[web3#toWei() doc v1.0.0](https://web3js.readthedocs.io/en/1.0/web3-utils.html#towei)

## üî¢ Code To Reproduce Issue 

```Javascript
const { BigNumber } = web3;
const { ether } = require('openzeppelin-solidity/test/helpers/ether');
const loger = require('mocha-logger');

require('chai')
    .use(require('chai-bignumber')(BigNumber))
    .should();

describe('I want to use helper method to convert ether value into wei', () => {
    it('should output 123456789012345678 wei when input is 0.123456789012345678 ether', async () => {
        const result = ether(0.123456789012345678);
        loger.log(`result is ${result}`); // result is 123456789012345680
        result.should.be.bignumber.equal(new BigNumber('123456789012345678'));
    });

    it('should output 123456789012345678 wei when input is string and equal to 0.123456789012345678 ether', async () => {
        const result = ether('0.123456789012345678');
        loger.log(`result is ${result}`); // result is 123456789012345678
        result.should.be.bignumber.equal(new BigNumber('123456789012345678'));
    });
});
```

## üëç Other Information

```Shell
 I want to use helper method to convert ether value into wei
    1) should output 123456789012345678 wei when input is 0.123456789012345678 ether
    ‚úì should output 123456789012345678 wei when input is string and equal to 0.123456789012345678 ether

1 passing (9s)
  1 failing

  1) I want to use helper method to convert ether value into wei
       should output 123456789012345678 wei when input is 0.123456789012345678 ether:

      AssertionError: expected '123456789012345680' to equal '123456789012345678'
      + expected - actual

      -123456789012345680
      +123456789012345678
```
